                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12719542" author="albegarcia" created="Mon, 15 Jun 2009 13:00:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have been debugging the sources of CXF and I think the problem is that the queues for executing the One-Way Web Services (class AutomaticWorkQueueImpl) aren&apos;t stopped (invoking the shutdown method of ThreadExecutorPool, its superclass) when Tomcat stop. I have done a test and if you create a ThreadExecutorPool and don&apos;t stop it invoking the shutdown method, then Tomcat doesn&apos;t stop right.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12761802" author="dkulp" created="Sat, 3 Oct 2009 03:12:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this still an issue with 2.2.3?    We changed the workqueues we use to use daemon threads which may help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767550" author="dkulp" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 21:14:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Marking resolved as it should now be fixed and no response/confirmation after two weeks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
